  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "Paidia is one pole of Roger Caillois\u0026rsquo;s paidia-ludus spectrum: unstructured, spontaneous, free-form play — play before it becomes a game. A child splashing in a puddle, a musician noodling without a score, a group of friends improvising a story with no rules. Paidia is characterized by joy, improvisation, and the absence of imposed constraints. It isn\u0026rsquo;t formless — it has its own internal logic — but that logic emerges from the activity rather than being imposed from outside. No one decides the rules of a daydream in advance.\n",
